folder: Jerome Street & Dumont Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
text:
562 Jerome St., west side, south of Dumont Ave., showing the Duryea house, built in 1740; it was reshingled in 1840, and again in 1920. It was still standing in 1924.

About 1890.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

folder: Jerome Street & Dumont Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
text:
(1)
562 Jerome Street, west side, south of Dumont Ave., showing the Livingston-Duryee house which was built in 1740. It formerly had a dutch roof which was subsequently shortened. The house was reshingled in 1840 and again in 1920. It was still standing in (1929).

1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2)
The same, showing the south side of the house.

1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(3)
The same, showing the rear of houses facing on Barbey Street.

1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(4)
The same, showing also a 4-story brick building at No. 890 Dumont Ave.

May 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
